summary: The document is an identification form related to the JFK assassination system, specifically an agent's report from INSCOM/CSF regarding David Reed Fromer, a selective service registrant. It details checks made with local agencies in Marin County, California, which disclosed no records on the subject. The document is marked as 'RELEASED WITH DELETIONS' and was last reviewed on 03/07/95.
key_findings: The document is part of the DOD-affiliated personnel incident investigations series.
No records were found on David Reed Fromer in the checked local agencies.
The document was originally classified but has been released with deletions.
The agent's notes mention that Mill Valley is in Marin County, California.
